TNOW = (datetime.datetime.now())
TFORMAT = '{:%d-%m-%Y_%H:%M:%S}'.format(TNOW)
print(TFORMAT)


TNOW = (datetime.datetime.now())
output = ("%.2i-%.2i-%.2i_%.2i:%.2i:%.2i" %(TNOW.day,TNOW.month,TNOW.year,TNOW.hour,TNOW.minute,TNOW.second))
print (output)


ssh-keygen -n 2048 -t rsa(press enter) then copy the directory location and append username(admin1) to it.

fold -f -w 70 admin1.pub or fold -w 70

ssh-keygen -f admin1.pub -l(used to verify the hash on the linux)

TO CREATE VIRTUAL ENVIRONMENT
(P3.7) root@kali:~/automation# virtualenv -p python3.7 P3.7 

FOR TEXTFSM TO WORK
export NET_TEXTFSM='/root/automation/TEXTFSM_GIT/ntc-templates/ntc_templates/templates/'
OR
export net_TEXTFSM='/root/automation/P3.7/TEXTFSM_GIT/ntc-templates/ntc_templates/templates/'

TO EXTRACT AND INSTALL DOWNLOADED ATOM TEXT EDITOR
dpkg -i (downloaded debian atom editor)


FOR SCP TO WORK:
aaa new-model
aaa session-id common
ip ssh version 2
ip scp server enable
aaa authentication login default local
aaa authorization exec default local none
